Blocks for API Builder
1. Start Point
Description: Starting point for any API, configure basic parameters such as headers and authentication.

2. HTTP Request
Description: Send a GET, POST, PUT, or DELETE request to a specified endpoint.

3. Response Formatter
Description: Format or edit the API response into the desired JSON or XML structure.

4. Data Mapping
Description: Transform and map incoming data to another format or structure.

5. Conditional Logic
Description: Add if/else structures to follow different paths based on data.

6. Loop
Description: Repeat actions over a list or dataset.

7. Validation
Description: Check if incoming data meets predefined rules.

8. Authentication
Description: Add an authentication step, such as OAuth or API keys.

9. Error Handling
Description: Define alternative actions in case of errors.

10. Data Storage
Description: Save data to a database or cache.

11. Webhook Listener
Description: Set up an endpoint to listen for incoming webhooks.

12. Timer/Delay
Description: Add a wait time or schedule an action.

13. External Service
Description: Call an external API or service and process the data.

14. Logging
Description: Add a block to log actions or data for debugging.

15. Calculation
Description: Perform calculations or manipulate numeric values (e.g., addition, subtraction).

16. Merge Data
Description: Combine data from multiple sources into a single object.

17. Split Data
Description: Split a dataset into smaller parts or arrays.

18. Header Configuration
Description: Add specific headers to a request or response.

19. Query Parameters
Description: Add dynamic or static query parameters to a request.

20. Response Generator
Description: Create a custom response for an endpoint.